    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect signaling procedure sequence in RF simulator initialization\n\n### Summary\nThe RF simulator's device initialization sequence was causing improper signaling flow due to function pointers being set before critical device fields were initialized. This led to segmentation faults when the simulator attempted to process 3GPP signaling messages.\n\nSpecifically, `device->trx_start_func` was being assigned before `device->priv` was set, causing `startServer` and `startClient` functions to access uninitialized memory when invoked during the RRC connection establishment phase.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure OAI gNB with RF simulator in server mode\n2. Launch UE with RF simulator in client mode\n3. Observe segmentation fault in `startServer` function when accessing `device->priv`\n4. Alternatively, see incorrect signaling sequence logs indicating premature function calls\n\n### Changes\n- `radio/rfsimulator/simulator.c`: Reordered initialization sequence in `device_init` to ensure `device->priv` and other critical fields are set before function pointers are assigned\n"
}